byline.original: By OTTO D. TOLISCHUS Wireless to THE NEW YORK TIMES

abstract: Under-Sec Welles Berlin visit plans; Berlin press continues war issues and peace terms discussions and explains Poland and Czecho-Slovakia annexation; Welles conf with Min to Switzerland Harrison
snippet: BERLIN, Feb. 29--United States Under-Secretary of State Sumner Welles is scheduled to arrive in Berlin tomorrow morning for the first stop in his tour of the capitals of Europe's warring nations....

headline.main: NO NAZI PEACE PLAN; But Visit Is Welcomed as Chance to Explain Reich's War Aims PRESS SUGGESTS TERMS Recognition of 'Lebensraum,' Return of Colonies and End of 'Plutocracy'

lead_paragraph: BERLIN, Feb. 29--United States Under-Secretary of State Sumner Welles is scheduled to arrive in Berlin tomorrow morning for the first stop in his tour of the capitals of Europe's warring nations.
